&lt;p data-start=&quot;122&quot; data-end=&quot;506&quot;&gt;We are seeking a Chief Financial Officer (CFO) to shape the financial strategy of our fast-growing company. In this critical leadership role, you will oversee all financial operations, drive strategic decision-making, and partner with the executive team to fuel growth and long-term value creation. This is a unique opportunity to influence the trajectory of our business, optimize performance, and play a central role in advancing our mission in the ESG software space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Reponsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Finance &amp;amp; Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a strategic partner to the CEO on financial planning, growth strategy, and capital allocation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and lead a high-performing finance organization, balancing rigor with agility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide financial insight and decision support across all business functions (Sales, Product, Operations, HR).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee revenue management, including forecasting, pricing strategies, contract renewals, and revenue recognition in compliance with accounting standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage procurement strategy and vendor relationships to optimize cost, risk, and operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fundraising &amp;amp; Investor Relations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead equity and debt fundraising processes, including VC rounds, extensions, and strategic financings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain investor materials (pitch decks, financial models, data rooms)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage relationships with existing and prospective investors, lenders, and financial advisors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own board and investor reporting, ensuring clarity, accuracy, and strategic insight&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;M&amp;amp;A and Corporate Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, evaluate, and execute M&amp;amp;A, partnership, and strategic investment opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead financial due diligence, valuation, deal structuring, and negotiations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee post-acquisition integration from a financial and operational perspective&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with legal, tax, and external advisors throughout transactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Operations &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own all core financial operations, including accounting, payroll, and statutory reporting across jurisdictions (as applicable).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure strong internal controls, compliance, and audit readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead tax planning and regulatory compliance, supporting operational scalability and risk mitigation.&lt;br&gt;Manage contract administration processes, ensuring timely renewals and alignment with revenue recognition policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Infrastructure &amp;amp; Systems&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and scale financial systems, processes, and reporting tools appropriate for a growing company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure data integrity, timely actionable financial reporting, and alignment with revenue management processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support operational scalability and readiness for future milestones (e.g., IPO, large acquisitions).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize procurement systems and workflows to drive efficiency and cost savings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
